{"ID":270238, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"238\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs237.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs239.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 238<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">men in that state of corruption of the Jewish church&mdash;that righteous persons could only deliver their\n  own souls<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span>&mdash;applied it to the present state of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints&mdash;said\n  if the people departed from the Lord,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> they must fall&mdash;that they were depending on the Prophet,\n  hence were darkened in their minds,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> in consequence of neglecting the duties devolving upon\n  themselves, envious towards the innocent, while they afflict the virtuous with their shafts of envy.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">There is another error which opens a door for the adversary to enter.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> As females possess refined\n  feelings and sensitiveness, they are also subject to overmuch zeal,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> which must ever prove\n  dangerous, and cause them to be rigid in a religious capacity&mdash;[they] should be armed with mercy,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span>\n  notwithstanding the iniquity among us.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Spirit of Forgiveness<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Said he had been instrumental in bringing iniquity to light<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span>&mdash;it was a melancholy thought and\n  awful that so many should place themselves under the condemnation of the devil,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> and going to\n  perdition.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> With deep feeling he said that they are fellow mortals, we loved them once, shall we not\n  encourage them to reformation? We have not yet forgiven them seventy times seven,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> as our Savior\n  directed; perhaps we have not forgiven them once. There is now a day of salvation<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> to such as\n  repent and reform;&mdash;and they who repent not should be cast out<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> from this society; yet we should\n  woo them to return<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> to God, lest they escape not the damnation of hell!<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> Where there is a mountain\n  top, there is also a valley&mdash;we should act in all things on a proper medium to every immortal spirit.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span>\n  Notwithstanding the unworthy are among us,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> the virtuous should not, from self-importance, grieve\n  and oppress needlessly, those unfortunate ones&mdash;even these should be encouraged to hereafter live\n  to be honored<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> by this society, who are the best portions of the community. Said he had two things\n  to recommend to the members of this society, to put a double watch over the tongue;<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> no organized\n  body can exist without this at all. All organized bodies have their peculiar evils, weaknesses<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> and\n  difficulties, the object is to make those not so good reform and return to the path of virtue that they\n  may be numbered with the good,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> and even hold the keys of power,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> which will influence to virtue\n  and goodness&mdash;should chasten and reprove,<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107457\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107457)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107457)\">Ezek. 14:14,20<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107270\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107270)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107270)\">Isa. 59:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107353\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107353)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107353)\">Jer. 17:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107399\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107399)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107399)\">Jer. 31:36<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107719\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107719)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107719)\">Mal. 2:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112787\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112787)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112787)\">Morm. 6:17<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113182\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113182)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113182)\">D&amp;C 10:2<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114706\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114706)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114706)\">D&amp;C 84:54,80<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116784\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116784)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116784)\">Moses 5:23<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109344\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109344)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109344)\">Rom. 10:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106882\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106882)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106882)\">Ps. 136:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <